---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { useTranslations } from '../../i18n/utils';

const lang = 'en';
const t = useTranslations(lang);
---

<Layout title={t('rules.title')} lang={lang}>
	<main class="content-page">
		<header class="hero-small">
			<a href="/king-cardgame/en/" class="back-link">← Back</a>
			<h1>{t('rules.title')}</h1>
			<p>{t('rules.intro')}</p>
		</header>

		<article class="rules-content">
			<section>
				<h2>What is King?</h2>
				<p>King is a trick-taking game for 4 players, played with a standard 52-card deck. The objective varies depending on the contract chosen for each round.</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>The "Aloja" Variant</h2>
				<p>In this traditional version, the game is divided into two main phases: Negatives and Positives.</p>
				
				<div class="rules-grid">
					<div class="rule-box">
						<h3>Negative Phase</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>No Tricks:</strong> Each trick taken costs points.</li>
							<li><strong>No Hearts:</strong> Hearts taken cost points.</li>
							<li><strong>No Queens:</strong> Each Queen taken costs points.</li>
							<li><strong>No King of Hearts:</strong> The King taken costs many negative points.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					<div class="rule-box">
						<h3>Positive Phase</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Trump Contracts:</strong> The player chooses a trump suit and tries to win as many tricks as possible.</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Strategy Tips</h2>
				<p>Keep track of played cards, especially during negative rounds. In King, knowing when to lose a trick is just as important as knowing when to win.</p>
			</section>
		</article>
	</main>
</Layout>

<style>
	.content-page {
		max-width: 1000px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 4rem 2rem;
	}

	.hero-small {
		margin-bottom: 4rem;
		text-align: center;
	}

	.back-link {
		color: var(--accent);
		text-decoration: none;
		display: block;
		margin-bottom: 2rem;
	}

	h1 {
		font-size: 3rem;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
		color: var(--accent);
	}

	.rules-content {
		line-height: 1.8;
		color: #ddd;
	}

	section {
		margin-bottom: 3rem;
	}

	h2 {
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(212, 175, 55, 0.2);
		padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}

	.rules-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
		gap: 2rem;
		margin-top: 2rem;
	}

	.rule-box {
		background: rgba(255,255,255,0.05);
		padding: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	h3 {
		color: white;
		margin-bottom: 1rem;
	}

	ul {
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
	}

	li {
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
	}
</style>
